<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-05T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-05T11:00:00-05:00" n="170" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 185.161/1:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-05T11:00:00-05:00">December 5, 1918—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1. French Government requested that <persName corresp="#p_GS1">Gompers</persName> be asked to go over soon as his influence would
                            be useful in Germany. Has President reached a decision as to this
                            matter?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>